virginia code page 1 state of virginia code title 18.2 crimes and offenses generally chapter 8 crimes involving morals and decency sec 18.2 361 crimes against nature if any person shall carnally know in any manner any brute animal or carnally know any male or female person by the anus or by or with the mouth or voluntarily submit to such carnal knowledge he or she shall be guilty of a class 6 felony provided that if a parent commits such an act with his or her child and such child is at least thirteen but less than fifteen years of age at the time of the offense such parent shall be guilty of a class 3 felony code 1950 sec 18.1 212 1960 c 358 1968 c 427 1975 cc 14 15 1977 c 285 1981 c 397
